<font size="2" color="#990000"><b>ARTS</b></font><br>




<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/01/22/arts/music/22JAZZ.html?todaysheadlines">Carnegie's Jazz Band: Assessing the Losses</a></b><br>
The Carnegie Hall Jazz Band, one of few active bands that are seedbeds for jazz composition, is being disbanded after this season, which is a shame.
<P>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/01/22/arts/theater/22CYMB.html?todaysheadlines">Shakespeare's Grab Bag, Globally Rendered</a></b><br>
"Cymbeline," now being brought delightfully to life by Bartlett Sher and  the Theater for a New Audience, is a kooky  grab bag of a play, a Shakespearean buffet.
<P>
</font>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/01/22/arts/theater/22POUN.html?todaysheadlines">A Comic's Hard Road Back to Work After Arrest</a></b><br>
Paula Poundstone, a comedian with an amiably witty style, was arrested for child abuse last June. Can she make a comeback?
<P>
</font>













<p>
